[2] USA (Connecticut)
Date: Tue 24 Jun 2014
Source: Eyewitness News 3 [edited - Mod.CP]
http://www.wfsb.com/story/25860264/middlesex-hospital-treats-possible-measles-case


Middlesex Hospital [Connecticut] said it became aware of a suspected case of measles in a patient in the emergency room on Sunday [22 Jun 2014]. The state's Department of Public Health was notified and is taking the necessary steps to address this situation, hospital officials said.

Staff, patients and guests were all alerted about the possible measles case, and continue to be informed, as the measles infection is highly contagious and can be caught by simply being in the presence of someone with measles. Anyone who contracted measles would see the 1st signs within 1 or 2 weeks. Symptoms include fever, spots which could sometimes be in the mouth, and a rash.

[Byline: Kaitlyn Naples]

