[6] North Korea (North Pyongan)
Date: Wed 25 Jun 2014
Source: Radio Free Asia (RFA) [summ., edited - Mod.CP]
http://www.rfa.org/english/news/korea/outbreak-06252014174732.html


A measles outbreak in a North Korean province bordering China has left at least 3 children dead this week in what is believed to be the worst attack of the highly contagious disease in 7 years. The deaths occurred on Monday [23 Jun 2014] after the disease, which mainly affects children, hit a district near Sinuiju, the capital of North Pyongan province in the northwest of North Korea and a gateway to China, a source told RFA's Korean Service. North Korean authorities have tried to hush up the outbreak and have blamed it on North Korean shipping crews traveling to and from China.

North Pyongan province is bounded by water on the west by the Korea Bay and the Yellow Sea, called the West Sea by Koreans. But the source said Pyongyang has imposed travel restrictions to contain the problem and the Ministry of Health has begun immunizing residents in Yongchun district and Sinuiju.

"Recently measles broke out in Yongchun district near Sinuiju and spread rapidly," the source said, speaking on condition of anonymity from Sinuiju, which borders China's Dandong city. According to the source, the measles outbreak was not reported by the North Korean media, and it is believed the North Korean Ministry of Health is keeping a tight lid on the issue to avoid being reprimanded "for failing to undertake anti-epidemic measures."

It is believed to be the worst outbreak in North Korea since 2007, when at least 4 people died. At that time, a massive vaccination campaign was initiated by the World Health Organisation in response to a significant measles outbreak in which 3500 cases were reported in 30 counties in all of North Korea's provinces, with densely populated areas particularly affected. To prevent measles from spreading, the North Korean government prohibited people living in south of Yongchun district from visiting Sinuiju and also prohibited residents living in Sinuiju from visiting Yongchun district," according to reports.

