[8] Belarus
Date: Thu 26 Jun 2014
Source: Naviny.by, Obshchestvo [in Russian, summ. & transl. - Mod.CP]
http://naviny.by/rubrics/society/2014/06/26/ic_news_116_438079/


On the eve of the World Ice Hockey Championship, which was held in Minsk from 9-25 May 2014, Belarusian epidemiologists warned of the possibility of importation into the country of measles and other infectious diseases and recommended the implementation of preventative vaccination, according to BelaPAN. Imported measles case[s] from Russia had been recorded in Minsk in April this year [2014]. On that occasion, measles was transmitted from these cases to 7 local people.

According to the local medical authorities, measles cases are regularly imported into Belarus on an annual basis. Thus in 2013, one resident of Minsk contracted measles in Ukraine and another in Russia. Last year [2013] in Minsk one unvaccinated child, less than 12 months in age, was identified and vaccinated. Measles vaccination is carried out in Belarus at 12 months with re-vaccination at 6 years. According to the World Health Organisation, measles cases in 2013 were reported in 36 countries of the European region and 31 617 cases were recorded. Most of these measles cases were recorded in Turkey and Ukraine among unvaccinated people.

