[11] Ukraine (Kharkov)
Date: Thu 26 June 2014
Source: Kharkov [in Russian, transl., edited - Mod.CP]
http://kharkov.comments.ua/news/2014/06/26/090052.html


Measles in Kharkov
------------------
According to City Watch, those affected are predominately people who have not been vaccinated previously. Furthermore, more than 40 percent belong to the migrant Roma population. Since the beginning of 2014 the Kharkov region has recorded more than 93 000 cases of infectious diseases. Although this represents a 9.3 percent decrease, the situation remains unsatisfactory. There have been decreases in the incidences of salmonellosis, shigellosis, respiratory tuberculosis, mumps, rubella, acute viral hepatitis B and C, and other infectious diseases.

However, in the Kharkov region, as well as in Ukraine in general, there has been an increased incidence of measles. The incidence has been sporadic in most cases. 6 family groups with 3-6 cases [each] have been identified. The vast majority of measles patients have not received vaccinations against measles, more than 40 percent in the case of those having Roma ethnicity.

